                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12965037" author="djencks" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 00:49:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in rev 1040364.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12965133" author="gerdogdu" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 07:16:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AFAIK those additions in ContextFactory was committed by Mark. I do not remember the reason &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12965139" author="gerdogdu" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 07:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have found the reason, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-369&quot; title=&quot;Static ContextsService in ContextFactory causes wrong webContextService used for multiple applications&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OWB-369&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OWB-369&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12965140" author="gerdogdu" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 07:44:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems that actual comment of that commit was &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-369&quot; title=&quot;Static ContextsService in ContextFactory causes wrong webContextService used for multiple applications&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OWB-369&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OWB-369&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; improve ContextsService retrieval&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Getting the ContextsService each time was very expensive.&lt;br/&gt;
We now cache it depending on the ClassLoader. This way&lt;br/&gt;
it is possible that different WebApps may configure &lt;br/&gt;
different ContextsServices.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12965141" author="gerdogdu" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 07:47:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trunk gives compile errors. I will correct them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12965148" author="gerdogdu" created="Tue, 30 Nov 2010 08:21:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Compiler errors fix in r1040432.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
